utinib, Lapatinib, Selumetinib, Ribociclib, Vandetanib, More', 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/93649/', '[1] Skinner MH, Kuan HY, Pan A, et al. "Duloxetine is both an inhibitor and a substrate of cytochrome P4502D6 in healthy volunteers." Clin Pharmacol Ther 73 (2003): 170-7[2] "Product Information. Cymbalta (duloxetine)." Lilly, Eli and Company, Indianapolis, IN.[3] "Product Information. Cymbalta (duloxetine)." Lilly, Eli and Company, Indianapolis, IN.', 1767369485);
